events.description: The Mesoamerican Long Count calendar, used by several pre-Columbian Mesoamerican civilizations, notably the Maya, begins.
events.html: • 3114 BC – The Mesoamerican Long Count calendar, used by several pre-Columbian Mesoamerican civilizations, notably the Maya, begins.

events.description: Traditional date of the defeat of Bel by Hayk, progenitor and founder of the Armenian nation.
events.html: • 2492 BC – Traditional date of the defeat of Bel by Hayk, progenitor and founder of the Armenian nation.

events.description: The south-western part of Dacia (modern Romania) becomes a Roman province: Roman Dacia.
events.html: • 106 – The south-western part of Dacia (modern Romania) becomes a Roman province: Roman Dacia.

events.description: Hadrian is proclaimed Roman emperor, two days after Trajan's death.
events.html: • 117 – Hadrian is proclaimed Roman emperor, two days after Trajan's death.[1]

events.description: Claudius Silvanus, accused of treason, proclaims himself Roman Emperor against Constantius II.
events.html: • 355 – Claudius Silvanus, accused of treason, proclaims himself Roman Emperor against Constantius II.

events.description: Battle of Adda: The Goths under Theodoric the Great and his ally Alaric II defeat the forces of Odoacer on the Adda River, near Milan.
events.html: • 490 – Battle of Adda: The Goths under Theodoric the Great and his ally Alaric II defeat the forces of Odoacer on the Adda River, near Milan.

events.description: The Qarmatians of Bahrayn capture and pillage the city of Basra.
events.html: • 923 – The Qarmatians of Bahrayn capture and pillage the city of Basra.[2]

events.description: The Great Famine of Europe becomes so dire that even the king of England has difficulties buying bread for himself and his entourage.
events.html: • 1315 – The Great Famine of Europe becomes so dire that even the king of England has difficulties buying bread for himself and his entourage.[3]

events.description: Wars of Scottish Independence: Battle of Dupplin Moor: Scots under Domhnall II, Earl of Mar are routed by Edward Balliol.
events.html: • 1332 – Wars of Scottish Independence: Battle of Dupplin Moor: Scots under Domhnall II, Earl of Mar are routed by Edward Balliol.

events.description: The Battle of Otlukbeli: Mehmed the Conqueror of the Ottoman Empire decisively defeats Uzun Hassan of Aq Qoyunlu.
events.html: • 1473 – The Battle of Otlukbeli: Mehmed the Conqueror of the Ottoman Empire decisively defeats Uzun Hassan of Aq Qoyunlu.

events.description: Rodrigo de Borja is elected as Head of the Catholic Church, taking the name Pope Alexander VI.
events.html: • 1492 – Rodrigo de Borja is elected as Head of the Catholic Church, taking the name Pope Alexander VI.[4]

events.description: Franco-Dutch War: Forces of the Holy Roman Empire defeat the French in the Battle of Konzer Brücke.
events.html: • 1675 – Franco-Dutch War: Forces of the Holy Roman Empire defeat the French in the Battle of Konzer Brücke.

events.description: Morean War: The 49-day Siege of Coron ends with the surrender and massacre of its garrison by the Venetians.
events.html: • 1685 – Morean War: The 49-day Siege of Coron ends with the surrender and massacre of its garrison by the Venetians.[5]

events.description: Captain Francis Light establishes the British colony of Penang in Malaysia.
events.html: • 1786 – Captain Francis Light establishes the British colony of Penang in Malaysia.

events.description: Francis II assumes the title of first Emperor of Austria.
events.html: • 1804 – Francis II assumes the title of first Emperor of Austria.

events.description: Peninsular War: French troops engage British-Portuguese forces in the Battle of Majadahonda.
events.html: • 1812 – Peninsular War: French troops engage British-Portuguese forces in the Battle of Majadahonda.

events.description: In Colombia, Juan del Corral declares the independence of Antioquia.
events.html: • 1813 – In Colombia, Juan del Corral declares the independence of Antioquia.

events.description: The Eiger in the Bernese Alps is ascended for the first time by Charles Barrington accompanied by Christian Almer and Peter Bohren.
events.html: • 1858 – The Eiger in the Bernese Alps is ascended for the first time by Charles Barrington accompanied by Christian Almer and Peter Bohren.

events.description: An explosion of guncotton occurs in Stowmarket, England, killing 28.
events.html: • 1871 – An explosion of guncotton occurs in Stowmarket, England, killing 28.[6][7]

events.description: Spanish–American War: American troops enter the city of Mayagüez, Puerto Rico.
events.html: • 1898 – Spanish–American War: American troops enter the city of Mayagüez, Puerto Rico.

events.description: World War I: The Battle of Amiens ends.
events.html: • 1918 – World War I: The Battle of Amiens ends.

events.description: Germany's Weimar Constitution is signed into law.
events.html: • 1919 – Germany's Weimar Constitution is signed into law.[8]

events.description: The 1920 Cork hunger strike begins which eventually results in the deaths of three Irish Republicans including the Lord Mayor of Cork Terence MacSwiney.
events.html: • 1920 – The 1920 Cork hunger strike begins which eventually results in the deaths of three Irish Republicans including the Lord Mayor of Cork Terence MacSwiney.[9]

events.description: The Latvian–Soviet Peace Treaty, which relinquished Russia's authority and pretenses to Latvia, is signed, ending the Latvian War of Independence.
events.html: • 1920 – The Latvian–Soviet Peace Treaty, which relinquished Russia's authority and pretenses to Latvia, is signed, ending the Latvian War of Independence.

events.description: Babe Ruth becomes the first baseball player to hit 500 home runs in his career with a home run at League Park in Cleveland, Ohio.
events.html: • 1929 – Babe Ruth becomes the first baseball player to hit 500 home runs in his career with a home run at League Park in Cleveland, Ohio.

events.description: The first civilian prisoners arrive at the Federal prison on Alcatraz Island.
events.html: • 1934 – The first civilian prisoners arrive at the Federal prison on Alcatraz Island.

events.description: Actress Hedy Lamarr and composer George Antheil receive a patent for a Frequency-hopping spread spectrum communication system that later became the basis for modern technologies in wireless telephones, two-way radio communications, and Wi-Fi.
events.html: • 1942 – Actress Hedy Lamarr and composer George Antheil receive a patent for a Frequency-hopping spread spectrum communication system that later became the basis for modern technologies in wireless telephones, two-way radio communications, and Wi-Fi.

events.description: Poles in Kraków engage in a pogrom against Jews in the city, killing one and wounding five.
events.html: • 1945 – Poles in Kraków engage in a pogrom against Jews in the city, killing one and wounding five.

events.description: Hussein bin Talal is proclaimed King of Jordan.
events.html: • 1952 – Hussein bin Talal is proclaimed King of Jordan.

events.description: Sheremetyevo International Airport, the second-largest airport in Russia, opens.
events.html: • 1959 – Sheremetyevo International Airport, the second-largest airport in Russia, opens.

events.description: Chad declares independence from France.
events.html: • 1960 – Chad declares independence from France.

events.description: The former Portuguese territories in India of Dadra and Nagar Haveli are merged to create the Union Territory Dadra and Nagar Haveli.
events.html: • 1961 – The former Portuguese territories in India of Dadra and Nagar Haveli are merged to create the Union Territory Dadra and Nagar Haveli.

events.description: Vostok 3 launches from the Baikonur Cosmodrome and cosmonaut Andrian Nikolayev becomes the first person to float in microgravity.
events.html: • 1962 – Vostok 3 launches from the Baikonur Cosmodrome and cosmonaut Andrian Nikolayev becomes the first person to float in microgravity.

events.description: Race riots (the Watts Riots) begin in the Watts area of Los Angeles, California.
events.html: • 1965 – Race riots (the Watts Riots) begin in the Watts area of Los Angeles, California.

events.description: The Apollo 11 astronauts are released from a three-week quarantine following their liftoff from the Moon.
events.html: • 1969 – The Apollo 11 astronauts are released from a three-week quarantine following their liftoff from the Moon.[10]

events.description: Vietnam War: The last United States ground combat unit leaves South Vietnam.
events.html: • 1972 – Vietnam War: The last United States ground combat unit leaves South Vietnam.

events.description: At the 1520 Sedgwick Avenue apartment building in The Bronx, New York, DJ Kool Herc hosts a house party widely considered to mark the birthplace of hip hop culture and music.  DJ Kool Herc demonstrates a new technique of beat juggling and Coke La Rock performs a new style of vocal performance called rapping.
events.html: • 1973 – At the 1520 Sedgwick Avenue apartment building in The Bronx, New York, DJ Kool Herc hosts a house party widely considered to mark the birthplace of hip hop culture and music. [11] DJ Kool Herc demonstrates a new technique of beat juggling and Coke La Rock performs a new style of vocal performance called rapping.

events.description: East Timor: Governor Mário Lemos Pires of Portuguese Timor abandons the capital Dili, following a coup by the Timorese Democratic Union (UDT) and the outbreak of civil war between UDT and Fretilin.
events.html: • 1975 – East Timor: Governor Mário Lemos Pires of Portuguese Timor abandons the capital Dili, following a coup by the Timorese Democratic Union (UDT) and the outbreak of civil war between UDT and Fretilin.

events.description: Two Aeroflot Tupolev Tu-134s collide over the Ukrainian city of Dniprodzerzhynsk and crash, killing all 178 aboard both airliners.
events.html: • 1979 – Two Aeroflot Tupolev Tu-134s collide over the Ukrainian city of Dniprodzerzhynsk and crash, killing all 178 aboard both airliners.

events.description: A bomb explodes on Pan Am Flight 830, en route from Tokyo, Japan to Honolulu, Hawaii, killing one passenger and injuring 15 others.
events.html: • 1982 – A bomb explodes on Pan Am Flight 830, en route from Tokyo, Japan to Honolulu, Hawaii, killing one passenger and injuring 15 others.

events.description: "We begin bombing in five minutes": United States President Ronald Reagan, while running for re-election, jokes while preparing to make his weekly Saturday address on National Public Radio.
events.html: • 1984 – "We begin bombing in five minutes": United States President Ronald Reagan, while running for re-election, jokes while preparing to make his weekly Saturday address on National Public Radio.

entities.name: We begin bombing in five minutes

events.description: A meeting between Sayyed Imam Al-Sharif, Osama bin Laden, Abdullah Yusuf Azzam, and leaders of Egyptian Islamic Jihad in Afghanistan culminates in the formation of Al-Qaeda.
events.html: • 1988 – A meeting between Sayyed Imam Al-Sharif, Osama bin Laden, Abdullah Yusuf Azzam, and leaders of Egyptian Islamic Jihad in Afghanistan culminates in the formation of Al-Qaeda.[12]

events.description: Nickelodeon's first line of “Nicktoons” (Doug, Rugrats & Ren & Stimpy) premiere on the channel.
events.html: • 1991 – Nickelodeon's first line of “Nicktoons” (Doug, Rugrats & Ren & Stimpy) premiere on the channel.

events.description: The Mall of America in Bloomington, Minnesota opens. At the time the largest shopping mall in the United States.
events.html: • 1992 – The Mall of America in Bloomington, Minnesota opens. At the time the largest shopping mall in the United States.[13]

events.description: An air rage incident occurs on board Southwest Airlines Flight 1763 when 19-year-old Jonathan Burton attempts to storm the cockpit, but he is subdued by other passengers and dies from his injuries.
events.html: • 2000 – An air rage incident occurs on board Southwest Airlines Flight 1763 when 19-year-old Jonathan Burton attempts to storm the cockpit, but he is subdued by other passengers and dies from his injuries.[14]

events.description: NATO takes over command of the peacekeeping force in Afghanistan, marking its first major operation outside Europe in its 54-year-history.
events.html: • 2003 – NATO takes over command of the peacekeeping force in Afghanistan, marking its first major operation outside Europe in its 54-year-history.

events.description: Jemaah Islamiyah leader Riduan Isamuddin, better known as Hambali, is arrested in Bangkok, Thailand.
events.html: • 2003 – Jemaah Islamiyah leader Riduan Isamuddin, better known as Hambali, is arrested in Bangkok, Thailand.

events.description: The oil tanker MT Solar 1 sinks off the coast of Guimaras and Negros Islands in the Philippines, causing the country's worst oil spill.
events.html: • 2006 – The oil tanker MT Solar 1 sinks off the coast of Guimaras and Negros Islands in the Philippines, causing the country's worst oil spill.

events.description: At least 306 people are killed and 3,000 others injured in a pair of earthquakes near Tabriz, Iran.
events.html: • 2012 – At least 306 people are killed and 3,000 others injured in a pair of earthquakes near Tabriz, Iran.

events.description: At least 41 people are killed and another 179 injured after two passenger trains collide in Alexandria, Egypt.
events.html: • 2017 – At least 41 people are killed and another 179 injured after two passenger trains collide in Alexandria, Egypt.

events.description: Luna 25 launches from the Vostochny Cosmodrome.
events.html: • 2023 – Luna 25 launches from the Vostochny Cosmodrome.[15]
